      <section class="section" id="atlantic-beach-faq">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>Atlantic Beach Paver Sealing Questions</h2>

          <div class="stack" style="margin-top:16px;">

            <details class="faq-item">
              <summary><strong>Do you seal pavers in Atlantic Beach year-round?</strong></summary>
              <div class="faq-body">
                <p class="muted">
                  Most of the year, yes. The limiting factor is moisture: rain forecasts, shaded areas that stay damp, and humidity. Near the coast,
                  we pay extra attention to dry-down so the sealer cures clean and even.
                </p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-item">
              <summary><strong>Why do coastal pavers get dark spots or slick growth?</strong></summary>
              <div class="faq-body">
                <p class="muted">
                  Coastal humidity and shade pockets let algae and mildew take hold faster—especially on patios, side yards, and north-facing areas.
                  Proper cleaning + sealing helps reduce absorption and makes ongoing maintenance a lot easier.
                </p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-item">
              <summary><strong>Can you seal pool decks without making them dangerously slippery?</strong></summary>
              <div class="faq-body">
                <p class="muted">
                  Yes, with the right approach. Slippery areas usually come from the wrong finish or heavy application. We keep coats controlled and can recommend
                  traction-friendly options when it makes sense for walking zones.
                </p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="faq-item">
              <summary><strong>What’s the fastest way to get a quote for Atlantic Beach?</strong></summary>
              <div class="faq-body">
                <p class="muted">
                  Text or submit your address in Atlantic Beach plus two photos (wide shot + joints). If you know approximate square footage, include it.
                  We’ll confirm prep requirements and send a clear quote.
                </p>
              </div>
            </details>

          </div>
